          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 12 3/4 in. by 8 5/8, consisting of 222 leaves, some
                                    of which are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 31, 59,
                                    68, 96, 107, 118, 221, and 222. The quires, signed with letters,
                                    were originally 24 in number, but the first two have been lost.
                                    A single leaf is wanting after fol. 31, and another after fol.
                                    168; and nearly the whole of fol. 145 has been torn out. Each
                                    page is divided into two columns of 25 lines.</p>
