              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" medium="unknown" scope="major" script="syr">
                This manuscript is written, by two persons, in a neat, regular
                character, with numerous Greek vowels (<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܱ ܷ ܻ ܴ ܾ</foreign>). Syriac vowels and the points rukkākh and ḳushshāi are more rare. </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="syr">
                The writer of the latter portion (foll. 169 —222) does not mention his
                           name. </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote3" medium="unknown" scope="minor" script="syr">
